Vice President Mike Pence spoke in Utah about the importance of passing the United States-Mexico-Canada Agreement (USMCA). He emphasized that the USMCA is a win for Utah and America, and urged Speaker Pelosi to put the agreement on the floor of Congress for passage. Pence also discussed the benefits of the USMCA in strengthening the US position in trade negotiations with other countries. He addressed concerns about passing the agreement in an election year and dismissed predictions of an economic downturn, highlighting the strong economy and job growth. Pence also touched on immigration, expressing the administration's commitment to securing the southern border and implementing a merit-based immigration system. He addressed the support for President Trump in Utah and emphasized the administration's accomplishments, including job creation, tax cuts, and conservative appointments to federal courts. Pence stated that he is honored to serve as Vice President and run as Trump's running mate again.